cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 

- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category, as the paper is focused on investigating the particularities of contemporary software systems and proposing a framework to support their engineering. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely, as the paper discusses the impact of these new types of applications on society and the need to revisit our traditional approach to software development. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories, as the paper deals with systems that are distributed and interconnected, and require smartness to support activities. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the integration of communication devices and technologies in these new types of applications.
